Creates an editable GnDataObject with data derived from a source GnDataObject.

Parameters:
{@link - GnAlbum}
Returns:
GnAlbumEdit

Remarks:

Use this function to create an editable GnDataObject from a source GnDataObject (TYPE_ALBUM). The editable GnDataObject is essentially a close copy (but not a clone) of the source GnDataObject, containing the metadata that is editable.

Note:

After the function has completed processing, the child's GnDataObject handle must be released

GnException

albumEditFromCdToc

public GnAlbumEdit albumEditFromCdToc(java.lang.String cdtoc)
                               throws GnException
Creates an editable Album GnDataObject to submit data for a specific GnDataObject context. The album comes pre-populated with the correct number of track children, but no metadata.

Parameters:
toc - set CD TOC string
Returns:
GnAlbumEdit

Remarks:

Use this function to create an editable album GnDataObject with the correct number of track children, as derived from the TOC. The children are empty, and do not have metadata. You must enter all the children's metadata.
Throws:
GnException

isAudioProcessNeeded

public boolean isAudioProcessNeeded(GnAlbum album,
                                    boolean bSubmitTestMode)
                             throws GnException
Prepares a parcel for gathering and generating features.

Parameters:
dataObject - set Handle to a GnDataObject; note that these are generally not editable GDOs
flags - set One of the available Submit Parcel Flags
Returns:
bool

Remarks:

Use this function to initialize the generation process for features contained in a parcel; this enables Gracenote Service to determine if it requires specific feature data from the parcel, such as a particular audio stream (Track). The function first checks whether the application's license has been enabled for Submit. If not, the function cancels. You can submit Track feature data only for Album GDOs that are generated from a TOC lookup. For an example of performing a TOC lookup, see Example: MusicID TOC Lookup.

Important:

Be sure to call DataInitFeature only once per Album.
Throws:
GnException

audioProcessInit

public void audioProcessInit(GnTrack track,
                             long audioRate,
                             GnSubmitAudioFormat audioFormat,
                             long audioChannels)
                      throws GnException
Initializes the generation of features for a specific audio stream.

Parameters:
track_num - set Ordinal for the audio stream (for albums, this is the track number)
audio_rate - set Sample rate of audio to be provided ( for example: 44100)
audio_format - set The audio format
audio_channels - set Number of channels for audio to be provided (for example: 2)

Remarks:

Use this function to initialize the generation of a specific audio stream (track). You must ensure the following successfully happens before calling this function: Calling the DataInitFeature function, so the Gracenote Service can identify which audio streams require processing. Initializing the DSP library, in preparation for track fingerprint generation.
Throws:
GnException

audioProcessFinalize

public void audioProcessFinalize(GnTrack track,
                                 boolean bAborted)
                          throws GnException
Finalizes the processing of the audio for the given stream.

Parameters:
abort - set Boolean value to indicate whether the finalization process must stop operating, due to processing errors

Remarks:

Use this function to finalize write processing for a feature. This function must be called before the feature can be uploaded. If your application receives an error or aborts while calling this function, be sure the application calls the upload function (upload). This ensures sending important information to Gracenote that is useful for error resolution.
Throws:
GnException
